Pump Industry News & Product Updates

We're on top of the pump industry news and product updates so you don't have to. Check back often for the latest pump industry information and make sure to subscribe to our RSS feed. Have company news or product announcements you want to include in this section? Send the release to editors-at-pumpscout.com.




Xylem to Participate in the U.S. Department of Commerce's Smart Cities Infrastructure Business Development Mission
February 20, 2016
The trade mission’s intent is to help U.S. companies launch or increase their business in India, which includes New Dehli, Mumbai, Chennai, and Vizag. Industries include systems and services in the safety and security, intelligent transportation, water, wastewater, and power sectors.


Xylem to Participate in the U.S. Department of Commerce's Smart Cities Infrastructure Business Development Mission
February 20, 2016
The trade mission’s intent is to help U.S. companies launch or increase their business in India, which includes New Dehli, Mumbai, Chennai, and Vizag. Industries include systems and services in the safety and security, intelligent transportation, water, wastewater, and power sectors.


EagleBurgmann Espey Introduces New Carbon Floating Ring Seal
February 18, 2016
The WD200/500 series can be used in industries that include chemistry, metal, cement, food, power station technology, mechanical, and plant engineering. They can seal flammable, acidic, toxic, and vaporous gasses, as well as liquid mist, oil mist, creeping oil, and water.


New Back Pressure Regulator Introduced by Cashco, Inc.
February 16, 2016
The new Model BR was created to be used with a wide range of gasses and liquids, making it ideal for many different applications.


Italian Compressor Manufacturer FIAC to Be Acquired by Atlas Copco
February 15, 2016
FIAC, founded in 1977, employs nearly 400 employees and has production sites in Italy, China, and Brazil.


Xylem Awarded a New Contract to Support Vietnam Water Treatment Plant Expansion
February 15, 2016
The pump manufacturer will design, install, and commission an expansion that will include the first ever ozone treatment application in Vietnam, enabling the Saigon Water Corporation’s Tan Hiep Water Treatment Plant 2 to produce 300,000 cubic meters of drinking water each day.


Compact API 674 Reciprocating Plunger Pumps Delivered to La Pampilla Refinery by Ruhrpumpen
February 12, 2016
The project includes replacing aging and unreliable equipment that pumps light cycle oil, which is one of the products that is produced during the fluid catalytic cracking reaction.


Amarinth Manufactures Titanium Pumps for ADMA-OPCO Umm Lulu Development Project 
February 09, 2016
The project is part of a strategic initiative to pump 1.75 million barrels of crude oil a day by 2017, eventually increasing Abu Dhabi’s total crude oil production to 3.5 million barrels a day.


Vertical Sealless Magnetic-Drive Pumps to Be Supplied to New Chemical Plant by Sundyne
February 06, 2016
The pump manufacturer will be providing four LMV-801S vertical inline sealless magnetic-drive pumps, which combines API 685 sealless magnetic-drive technology with Sundyne API 610 OH3 and OH5 vertical direct drive pump hydraulics and wet end technology to create a brand new, high-efficiency product.


Morgan Advanced Materials Manufactures Ceramic Components for ADCP Transducers
February 04, 2016
Acoustic Doppler Current Profilers (ADCPs) have been on the market for many years, but new developments have greatly improved the efficiency and versatility of this technology. 


Verderflex Peristaltic Pumps Used in Hydrocell Wastewater Sampler System by Smart Storm
February 02, 2016
The pumping solution offers reliability, accuracy, and the ability to lift effluent up to 7 meters, before being measured and analyzed, with no need for a secondary pump. 


New Contracts Totaling $7.6 Million Awarded to H2O Innovation
January 29, 2016
The three contracts come from Englishman River Water Service, Valencia Water Reclamation Plant of the Sanitation Districts of Los Angeles County, and Lower Fort Garry in Manitoba. 


New Envelope PumpsUnveiled by Armstrong at AHR Expo 2016
January 27, 2016
The Generation 3 expands Armstrong’s innovative DE technology, which has saved building owners all over the world millions of dollars over the years. The new pumps will further increase energy savings while providing a more sustainable solution at the same time.


HVAC Combination Variable Frequency Drives Introduced by Fuji Electric
January 26, 2016
The FRENIC-HVAC Combination VFDs include “As-Built” CAD drawings, which are ideal for a wide range of applications that include food processing and pump control. 


Pentair to Provide Filtered Drinking Water at Minnesota Vikings' New U.S. Bank Stadium
January 23, 2016
The water technology company is set to be the Official Sustainable Water Partner of the professional football team for its efforts in cutting back on bottled water use.


34 Water Transfer Pumps Donated by Franklin Electric for Future Flood Relief Efforts
January 21, 2016
The City of Fort Wayne received the high volume water transfer pumps as a donation from Franklin Electric. 


Eccentric Disc Pump Technology Is Outperforming the Competition
January 20, 2016
Mouvex technology was tailored to meet the needs of the Western European oil and gas chemical markets with a unique design that enables the pump to transfer materials without the risk of shearing. This year, Mouvex’s landmark product line, the A Series Eccentric Disc Pump, celebrates its 50th anniversary.


Xylem Pump Technology to Increase Connectivity between Northern and Southern Europe
January 18, 2016
A new state-of-the-art water pumping station will expand the Lanaye Locks in Belgium, increasing connectivity between Northern and Southern Europe.


VerderFlex Offers Peristaltic Pumps for Reliable Wastewater Performance
January 15, 2016
Verderflex pumps' vertical lift capacity of nine meters far exceeds that of other manufacturers’ pumps; they also provide reliable and durable operation.


Sealed Internal Gear Pumps from EnviroGear Tackle Challenging Applications
January 12, 2016
The new internal gear pumps are especially suited to applications that deal with a wide range of viscosities, including higher viscosity applications.


Prevent Winter Flooding with a Submersible Pump
January 11, 2016
During flooding season, submersible pumps can quickly clear away water before causing lasting and expensive damage. Submersible pumps are designed to work underwater, so they are sealed to prevent water damage that would affect internal components. 


The Global Subsea Pumps Market Is a Growth Area in the Oil and Gas Industry
January 09, 2016
Oil prices are expected to stabilize by the end of 2017 and reach $80 per barrel by 2018. Subsea boosting is the single largest application, holding more than half of the market in 2014.


S Series Screw Pumps Released Globally by Blackmer
January 07, 2016
The S Series screw pump line is ideal for a variety of applications and can be configured based on several optional features. 


SLOW Series Pumps Introduced by Shanghai Liancheng for Firefighting Applications
January 04, 2016
The SLOW series centrifugal pumps are single-stage double suction split volute pumps, ideal for use in firefighting, shipbuilding, water transportation, building and many more applications. 


Generation 3 Design Envelope Pumps from Armstrong Set to Be Featured at AHR Expo 2016
January 01, 2016
The pumps feature 33 advanced models that offer energy savings and come in sizes from 1 to 75HP. The new generation of pumps are designed to increase energy savings even more while providing more sustainable solutions at the same time.


NPH and XH Series of Sliding Vane Pumps Introduced by Blackmer
December 29, 2015
The XH Series is designed to handle many different products, including a wide range of non-corrosive and non-abrasive industrial liquids and petroleum. The NPH Series of pumps is ideal when it comes to handling viscous and shear-sensitive fluids. 


Xylem Uses Advanced Pump Technology to Increase Connectivity at Belgium's Lanaye Locks
December 26, 2015
Flygt pumps and turbines will manage water levels in the canals while harnessing energy from excess water located in the Albert Canal. With the addition of a fourth lock, the system’s convoy capacity will quadruple.


Danfoss Breaks Ground on Development Center for Testing HVACR Equipment
December 23, 2015
The Engineering Tomorrow Application Development Center will be 22,000 square feet at its completion and located in Tallahassee, Florida. Three sets of psychometric rooms in the new facility will have the ability to test a wide variety of air-conditioning systems, including residential rooftop units from 2.5 to 50 tons and air-cooled chillers up to 150 tons.


200 KSB Pumps to Be Supplied to 3 Egyptian Power Stations
December 19, 2015
The order includes 36 boiler feed pumps, 24 condensate pumps, 8 cooling water pumps, and 132 process pumps. Each of the 36 boiler feed pumps can cover flow rates of up to 500 cubic meters per hour with heads of 2,000 meters and more.


$5 Million Granted to Joint Base San Antonio to Resolve Critical Water Needs
December 17, 2015
The funds will provide additional support in vital resources which will ensure that the military bases in the area can continue to serve local and national needs.

